    &lt;CommentText&gt;We were sorry to hear that your experience was not as positive as we would hope on 16th July 2019 at the Manchester Royal Infirmary. It is important to us that comments are heard and seen as an opportunity provided to the service to make changes and improvements wherever possible.

The Matron for the Emergency Department (ED) would like to apologise for the length of your wait and has advised the department was extremely busy when you attended. We would like to reassure you that the department has an established system to ensure patients are treated as quickly and safely as possible according to their clinical need. We are sorry if the expected waiting time was not effectively communicated to you.  

We take all issues surrounding patient care very seriously, if you would like to discuss this with us in more detail, please feel free to contact our Patient Advice and Liaison Service on 0161 276 8686 or by e-mailing pals@mft.nhs.uk, quoting reference number PO19/0076.&lt;/CommentText&gt;
